<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 4:29PM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of eastern Portage,
Trumbull, Mahoning, Geauga, northeastern Lake, northeastern Stark and
Ashtabula Counties through 530 PM EDT...
At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Fairport Harbor to near Minerva. Movement
was east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail. Some rotation
may be seen as well.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Youngstown, Warren, Painesville, Ashtabula, Conneaut, Salem,
Columbiana, Chardon, Geneva-On-The-Lake, Boardman, Alliance, Niles,
Campbell, Hubbard, Canfield, Cortland, Geneva, Newton Falls, Sebring
and Minerva.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
